TSXV/AIM-listed Mkango Resources has taken a progressive approach to developing its Malawi-based Songwe Hill rare earths project, focusing on ensuring a timeously delivered project that guarantees the best economics and financial returns for its stakeholders, writes Laura Cornish. This article first appeared in Mining Review Africa Issue 10 2018. It will be published online on the 7th November 2018. You can read the full digital magazine here or subscribe here to receive a print copy